    <body>
      <section eId="sec_2_30">
        <num>2.30</num>
        <heading>Training requirements for peace officers</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2_30__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>during the holder's continuous service as a peace officer; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2_30__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>for two years after the date of the commencement of an\ninterruption in such service where the holder had, immediately prior to\nsuch interruption, served as a peace officer for less than two\nconsecutive years; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2_30__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>for four years after the date of the commencement of an\ninterruption in such service where the holder had, immediately prior to\nsuch interruption, served as a peace officer for two consecutive years\nor longer.\n  As used in this subdivision, the term "interruption" shall mean a\nperiod of separation from employment as a peace officer by reason of\nsuch officer's leave of absence, resignation or removal, other than\nremoval for cause.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
